article.headline: Robert Morris 95, Wagner 90
article.story: CORAOPOLIS, Pa. (AP) -- A.J. Jackson scored 27 points and had 11 rebounds Derek Coleman had 25 points to lead Robert Morris to a 95-90 victory over Wagner on Monday. Jackson and Coleman led five players scoring in double figures for Robert Morris (6-5). Jeremy Chappell had 17, Tony Lee had 14, and Cori Boston added 11. Mark Porter had 19 points to lead Wagner (7-3), which also had four players score in double figures. Vincent Durell had 18, James Ulrich and DeEarnest McLemore each had 17 and Joey Mundweiler added 15. In a game that saw 19 lead changes, the Colonials put the Seahawks away with a 6-0 run in the last 25 seconds.
